04023nam a22004935i 9781399503976DE-B159720240306125748.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20122012stk    fo  d z      eng d  a97813995039767 a10.1515/97813995039762doi  a(DE-B1597)619486  a(OCoLC)1312727364  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  astkcGB-SCT 7aLCO0000002bisacsh1 aMansfield, Katherine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Collected Fiction of Katherine Mansfield, 1898-1915 /cKatherine Mansfield, Gerri Kimber, Vincent O'Sullivan. 1aEdinburgh : bEdinburgh University Press, c[2012] 4c©2012  a1 online resource (528 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aThe Edinburgh Edition of the Collected Works of Katherine Mansfield : EECWKM00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgements -- tAbbreviations and Textual Note -- tChronology -- tIntroduction -- tFiction 1898–1915 -- t1898 -- t1899 -- t1901 -- t1903 -- t1904 -- t1905 -- t1906 -- t1907 -- t1908 -- t1909 -- t1910 -- t1911 -- t1912 -- t1913 -- t1914 -- t1915 -- tAppendix A: Plan of Maata -- tAppendix B: Unpublished stories in King’s College London Archives -- tIndex of First Lines -- tIndex of Stories0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe resurgence of interest in Katherine Mansfield (1888-1923) in recent years has grown to the extent that she is now perceived as 'the most emblematic woman writer of her time'. Mansfield researchers have been frequently frustrated by the lack of a complete edition of her fiction. There are several editions of her stories in print, but these omit many pieces not already collected and published in the volumes edited by Mansfield's husband John Middleton Murry after her death, from which present 'collected' editions derive.This Edinburgh edition of her stories, published to coincide with the ninetieth anniversary of her death in 1923, is a truly complete collection of the author's fiction writing. The editors have sought to include hitherto uncollected or rarely seen stories and prose fragments as well as the instantly recognisable stories. Placed in chronological order and fully annotated with clear, concise notes, this edition undertakes a complete remapping of the author's fiction output, from her earliest childhood pieces to the pitch-perfect quality of the mature writer at the height of her craft, thereby redefining Katherine Mansfield as a writer for the twenty-first century.Key Features:Brings together all of Mansfield's extant fictionRefocuses critical attention on one of the most influential exponents of modernist fictionThe essential Mansfield text for individual scholars working on Mansfield studies, as well as those with a more general interest in Mansfield the writerRedefines Mansfield as a writer for the next generation  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / General.2bisacsh1 aKimber, Gerri, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aO'Sullivan, Vincent, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cprintz978074864274840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978139950397640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781399503976423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781399503976/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles